Text.Value: Let's get some rest. Dawn comes sooner than we think.
I have reason to believe the parasite is touched by Netherese magic.
Heh. I speak out of curiosity, not wishful thinking. At least I'll know to skip supper if you're doing the cooking.
Courage in danger's shadow. I love to see it.
How do you feel?

EditorData.NodeContext: A leading question. A little bit of pause after the comma, and then a bit slower to end.

Text.Value: Before the illithids' unscheduled surgery, I'd felled hundreds of beasts and a fair few fiends.
We could conjecture all night. I suppose the 'why' doesn't matter so much as the 'what next'.
Healthy. And troubled by that fact.
Ah, there it is - that shiver. Our little brain-worms have made fast friends, it would seem.
'Surprising' is just the word, isn't it?
Indeed. Perhaps the worms' vat was poisoned. Perhaps we're uncommonly fit.
There are others, too - these 'True Souls' that worship the Absolute.
And that answer is plain as the horns on a wardevil's head: we get these things out.
It makes no sense, I know. Why haven't we turned?
*A tingle runs through your head and down to your feet.*
But shouldn't the shadow have crept closer, gone darker by now?
Netherese? Ancient magic, that. Netheril is a memory so distant, I wager even you elves have forgotten.
Netherese? Ancient magic, that. Netheril is a memory so distant, I wager even the elves have forgotten.
Surprisingly fine, in spite of it all.
I'm more interested in how you feel.
Perhaps the worms' vat was poisoned. Perhaps we're uncommonly fit.
We could probably dig up some poison mushrooms, if you're that keen to be sick.
The tadpole's weakened me, suppressed greater talents. But beyond that -
Confident. No tiny tadpole will be getting the best of me.
I've shown no sign of turning. No nausea, no pain, not even a hot flash.
Something's special about us. Or at least, about our tadpoles.
Or perhaps the tadpoles are merely on holiday.
Not the best company to be sharing. Blessedly, their god's remained quiet to us.
Nervous. I don't like the idea of that thing in my brain.
It's natural, to suffer a touch of worry. But an illithid worm should be causing more than mild anxiety.

Synopsis: Wyll's CRD directly after recruitment, in which you can discuss the tadpole.
